title: Kate Hudson on Rachael Ray Show February 15, 2008
description:
Recommended links:
http://www.rockabyebabymusic.com/
http://www.jcp.com/
http://www.shopnewskool.com/

The beautiful Kate Hudson tells Rachael how she and Fool's Gold co-star Matthew McConaughey have become like brother and sister after working together in two films. "We really drive each other crazy," she says. "We really know how to push each other's buttons." Rach asks, "So ... who wins?"

"Well, me of course!" jokes Kate. "Women always win -- it's just a matter of time. We might let them win sometimes, but eventually we take the cake." All ribbing aside, Kate says she's excited about Matthew becoming a dad. "I think he's going to be a wonderful father," she says.

When talking about her own child, Kate opens up about the effect that the paparazzi have had on her family. "It bothers me, it bothers my parents," she says. "Ryder doesn't know what that is -- he's 4 years old. It's aggressive and it's bizarre to him and it makes him self-conscious. Kids should always be kids. They should never be self-conscious of what they're doing, ever." Kate says that this kind of aggressive behavior should be illegal. "As far as I'm concerned, a kid should just be allowed to be a kid."

title: Here's What Happens To The Leftover Food From Rachael Ray's Show
description:
When you watch Rachael Ray make a meal that could feed a big family on her "The Rachael Ray Show," you may wonder where all the food she made ends up. The audience actually can't eat that food, unfortunately, for insurance reasons. And the crew eats some, but it's often too much even for them. So where does it go?

You'll be pleased to know that it doesn't go to waste. The show partners with a local New York charity to make sure that the food Ray whips up goes to people that need it. Here's what happens to the leftover food from Rachael Ray's show.

description:

title: Co-Hosting the Rachael Ray Show | Jesse Palmer Vlog | Episode 04
description:
Iâ€™ll always jump at the chance to join my dear friend, the one and only Rachael Ray on her show, Rachael Ray Show. Luckily I get the chance to co-host it a few times a year and it's always a blast! The place is filled with excitement, great food, energy, and a fun and engaged live audience. And if one thing is for sure after being on this show, it's that I always leave the building feeling extremely full from the incredible food I get to taste and the inspiring conversations we get to have. This time around I was treated to AT LEAST five full meals as we featured guests from New York City's most popular new restaurants like Misi and Olmsted, and we even got to feed the crowd some treats. And as a special bonus after we wrapped, Rachael was kind enough to give both me AND you some inside access, where I picked her brain on her future aspirations, career journey, an what sheâ€™s working on.
